IAM:- 

IAM  stand for identity acess managment
that helps you securely manage acess to aws resouces 
it allows you to crate user, group,and roles
use iam to control what is authentication and authorization

AUTHENTICATION:- to check user are sign or not

AUTHERORIZARION:- to check user has permission acess to required or not

features of IAM :-
----------------

1) user managment
2) groups managment
3) roles and permissions
4) iam polices
5) mfa (multi factor authentication)
6) free to use

compoonwnts of IAM:- 

1) USER:-
        individual aws accounts for people for people or application

2)GROUP:-
       collection of user with similar permission

3)roles:-
        temporary permission assigned to user or services

4)polices:-
         json document that define permission.
